## Git workflow rules (local-only for now)

### Goal

- Use git to **track work locally** (history + diffs) even before GitHub exists.
- **Do not push** to any remote unless the user explicitly asks.

### Do

- Create commits in small logical chunks (docs vs code vs infra).
- Use clear messages (why > what).
- Keep generated artifacts out of git:
  - `uploads/**` (except `uploads/templates/**`)
  - caches (`__pycache__`, `.venv`, `.pytest_cache`, `.ruff_cache`, etc.)

### Don’t

- Don’t add a remote or push unless asked.
- Don’t commit secrets (`config.yaml`, api keys, tokens).
- Don’t commit large datasets/exports.

